ccsgp_get_started
-----------------

install virtualenv if you haven't yet. With MacPorts:
$ sudo port install py27-virtualenv

then:
$ git clone gitlab:github/ccsgp_get_started.git --recursive
$ cd ccsgp_get_started/
$ virtualenv-2.7 env
$ ./pip install -U numpy
$ ./pip install -U -r requirements.txt
$ ./python -m pyana -h
$ ./python -m pyana <country-initial>

produce all plots:
$ for i in `find examplesDir/input/examples/gp_datdir/* -type d`; do ./python -m pyana `basename $i`; done
$ open examplesDir/examples/gp_datdir/*.pdf

make_plot example function call in pyana/examples/gp_datdir.py.
symlink pyanaDir to somewhere else to get started on your own data.

if you like to write output to HDF5, you'll have to install the HDF5 libraries. With MacPorts:
$ sudo port install hdf5
it's not "switched on" right now. If you want to use it, uncomment the h5py
requirement in requirements.txt and rerun `./pip install -r requirements.txt`.
